- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is also a likely category as the paper adapts two real quantifier elimination methods, which are commonly used in symbolic computation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as conflict set computation is a key technique in automated reasoning and constraint solving, which are important areas in AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves algorithmic techniques for solving polynomial constraints. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a less likely category, but still possible as cylindrical algebraic decomposition is a technique used in computational geometry for solving systems of polynomial equations.
